  matters:"Muttaburrasaurus is a working demonstration that a fossil's story does not end at its first description. Sixty-three years after a grazier found it washed into marine rock, new scanning technology is still extracting substantial new biology - diet, brain shape, sense of smell - from the same bones, while the animal's place on the family tree remains an open, actively argued question rather than a settled fact.",
  fossilRecord:{
