    note:"The holotype (QM F10329) was discovered in 1964 and formally described by Ralph Molnar in 1980, making it the first ankylosaur described from the Southern Hemisphere. A more complete specimen (QM F18101) found in 1989 near Richmond was preliminarily referred to Minmi sp. and became the basis for most popular reconstructions and museum casts circulated under that name; a full 2015 description by Leahey et al. found it sufficiently distinct to warrant the new genus Kunbarrasaurus, restricting Minmi paravertebra to its original, more fragmentary holotype material. Six to seven specimens in total are attributed to the genus, most undescribed in detail."
  },
