  matters:"Kronosaurus shows how a spectacular museum mount can outrun the evidence supporting it: the plaster additions that made the Harvard skeleton famous also made it wrong, and correcting the record took decades. It is also a rare case where even the animal's name is still being argued over in the technical literature - not because anyone doubts a giant pliosaur existed in Cretaceous Australia, but because pinning a name precisely to a fragmentary holotype is a difficult problem.",
