  matters:"Massospondylus shows how even a long-settled scientific story can become unsettled again. A locomotor-shift hypothesis, repeated in books and documentaries for nearly two decades, is currently being actively re-argued in the technical literature using new anatomical evidence - proof that having an exceptional fossil record, embryos included, doesn't guarantee a fixed final answer.",
  fossilRecord:{
    knownFrom:"Numerous skeletons spanning embryos to adults; multiple egg clutches with embryos from Golden Gate Highlands National Park; a designated neotype skeleton",
