     why:"The species is known from very limited material, so any length estimate depends heavily on comparison with more completely known relatives.",
     interps:[
       ["14.4-15.1 m","conf-strong","A 2023 peer-reviewed CT-based reconstruction (Moore et al.) scaled the known vertebrae and cervical rib length against close relatives with complete necks, arriving at this range."],
       ["Up to 18 m, with a 35 m total body length","conf-low","Based on two isolated vertebrae from the same formation that have not been formally described and cannot yet be confirmed as belonging to this species."]
     ]},
    {q:"Is Mamenchisaurus a single natural group?",
     why:"Species were assigned to the genus over several decades based on general similarity, before modern phylogenetic methods could test the relationships directly.",
     interps:[
       ["No - the genus is not monophyletic","conf-moderate","Multiple recent phylogenetic analyses recover different named Mamenchisaurus species in different parts of the sauropod tree, though researchers have retained the name pending a full revision."],
       ["Yes, pending further study","conf-low","The traditional view, reflecting the genus's use since 1954 rather than a specific phylogenetic result supporting unity."]
