  ],
  matters:"Dilong overturned an assumption built entirely from its more famous relatives: that tyrannosaurs were, and always had been, scaly giants. Direct evidence of feathers turned up not in a large species but in one of the group's smallest and earliest known members, a reminder that the image built from the most famous specimens isn't always the full picture.",
  fossilRecord:{
    knownFrom:"At least four specimens, including a nearly complete holotype skeleton, from the Lujiatun Unit of the Yixian Formation",
