       ["Synonyms or variation within one species","conf-moderate","Several subsequent researchers have suggested the observed differences fall within the range of individual or growth-stage variation expected within a single species, given the modest sample sizes involved."]
     ]}
  ],
  matters:"Jeholornis shows that 'primitive' and 'advanced' are not opposites in evolution: the same animal carried an ancestral, dinosaur-like tail and a fully capable flight anatomy at once. It is also a useful case for a separate, less glamorous kind of scientific work - deciding how many species a fossil sample represents is its own real challenge, distinct from studying anatomy itself.",
  fossilRecord:{
