    locality:"Dinosaur Park Formation, Alberta, Canada",
    formation:"Dinosaur Park Formation",
    material:["Nearly complete skeletons","Skulls","Growth series from juvenile to adult","Vertebrae","Limb elements"],
    note:"Gorgosaurus libratus was discovered in 1913 by Charles M. Sternberg and formally described by Lawrence Lambe in 1914. A smaller specimen (AMNH 5664) was described as a new species, G. sternbergi, in 1923, but is now regarded as a juvenile G. libratus. Currie's 2003 study identified specific autapomorphies distinguishing Gorgosaurus from Albertosaurus, though some researchers continue to treat the two as synonymous. A 2019 reassessment (Voris et al.) re-examined a specimen (TMP 1994.143.1) long identified as a juvenile Daspletosaurus and reassigned it to juvenile Gorgosaurus libratus, after a properly diagnostic juvenile Daspletosaurus postorbital bone became available for direct comparison."
